<subSubSection id="C3196578FF95FFC45C89FC778D4D0862" pageId="4" pageNumber="117" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BBC36F3FF95FFC45C89FC778D4D0862" blockId="4.[166,1226,638,1112]" pageId="4" pageNumber="117">D i a g n o s i s. This species can be recognized from the combination of strongly shining anepisternum and postpronotal, presutural supra-alar, and katepisternal setae lacking; frons entirely black, without differentiated orbital setae.</paragraph>
